A 35-year-old petrol attendant, Elijah Chinonso has been arraigned before an Ile-Ife Magistratesâ€™ Court for alleged fraud. The accused person committed the offence in June 2021, at Metro Filling Station, Ede Road in Ile-Ife. The prosecutor, Inspector Sunday Osanyintuyi, told the court that the accused person, an attendant at the filling station, failed to remit the sum of N550,000 being sales for the month of June and fraudulently converted the money to his personal use. The offence committed contravened Sections 383(3) and 390(9) of the Criminal Code, Laws of Osun, 2021. The accused person who is facing a charge of fraud, however, pleaded not guilty to the charge levelled against him. The defence counsel, Mr Olalekan Babatunde, prayed the court to grant his client bail in liberal terms, promising that he would not jump bail. Magistrate Adewumi Oyebadejo granted the accused person bail in the sum of N100,000 with two sureties in like sum. Oyebadejo added that the sureties must swear to an affidavit of means, reside within the court jurisdiction and produce three recent passport photographs each. The case was adjourned till August 9, for hearing.